'''Viktor Bulatov''' (born [[January 22]] [[1972]]) is a  former [[Russia national football team|Russian]] international [[football (soccer)|football]]er.<br /><br />
Bulatov spent the prime years of his career at [[FC Spartak Moscow|Spartak Moscow]]. Apart from Spartak, Bulatov played for various [[Russia]]n clubs, including [[FC Torpedo Moscow|Torpedo Moscow]], [[FC Terek Grozny|Terek Grozny]], [[FC Alania Vladikavkaz|Alania Vladikavkaz]] and had two spells at [[FC Krylia Sovetov Samara|Krylia Sovetov]]. <br />
In summer 2007 as experienced player he moved to [[Kazakhstan|kazakh]] champions [[FC Astana|Astana]]<ref>[http://www.goal.com/ru/Articolo.aspx?ContenutoId=352866] "Bylatov moves to Astana" from Goal.com </ref> to streghten the club in forthcoming [[UEFA Champions League 2007-08|Champions League]] journey.

On international level, Bulatov made his debut for [[Russia national football team]] in a 1998 friendly match defeat to [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] and played his last game in 2001, against [[Greece national football team|Greece]].

